                        <h2>The Core Trade-Off: Quality vs Cost</h2>
                        <p>Lemlist and Saleshandy represent two distinct philosophies in cold email. Lemlist is built around the premise that personalization drives reply rates — and that higher reply rates justify a higher per-user price. Saleshandy is built around the premise that unlimited accounts at the lowest cost is the right foundation for high-volume outbound.</p>
                        <p>Both are correct, for different use cases. A solo founder or a 2-person SDR team running 200 highly personalized emails per week will likely get better results from Lemlist. An agency managing cold email campaigns for 10 clients across 30 domains will almost certainly get better economics from Saleshandy.</p>
